Looks like you ran out of memory. Are you using the default memory for the VM? 
To run Eclipse, you need to set the VM to use at least 256MB. Add the line -
Xmx256M to the end of the command you use to launch Eclipse.

I'm moving this to UI since there is no mention of CVS in the tracebacks. The 
error should probably be a bit more informative when an out-of-memory occurs 
(I assuming the error dialog said "Internal Error"). It probably should 
explicitly mention that Eclipse has run out of memeory.

This is again a problem with insufficient information about OOM Exception.

*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of bug 33972 ***
